11) Oxygen</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step6"><label>DURING â€“PROCEDURE Provide colonic wash using formula of salts like sodium sulphate and poly ethylene glycol (peg)that is dissolved in 5 liters of water to be administered on previous evening between 5pm and 9 pm, and 2.5 liters of solutions to be administered in the morning between 5 am and 8am</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step7"><label>Advice the patient to take clear fluids like glucose water, tender coconut water and peg preparation</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step8"><label>Give pre medication prescribed</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step9"><label>Make patient lie in left lateral position with lower limbs flexed at hip and and knee and buttocks at the table edge</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step10"><label>Assist doctor to perform digital examination and insert lubricated colonoscope into rectum</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step11"><label>Instruct patient to make slow deep breaths while scope is being inserted</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step12"><label>When the instrument reaches the sigmoid junction, the patient may be assisted to supine position to aid in the advance of the scope-past the splenic flexure</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step13"><label>Apply pressure to area of abdomen as directed by physician as he passes scope through splenic flexure, transverse colon and hepatic flexure into the ascending colon and cecum</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step14"><label>Monitor vital signs, color, warmth, level of consciousness, pain tolerance and observe for dryness of skin and abdominal distention</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step15"><label>POST-PROCEDURE CARE Monitor and document vital signs every 15 minutes for 1hour and then 30 minutes for the next 2 hours</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step16"><label>Observe signs of complications like bleeding, vomiting, severe and persistent abdominal pain, distention and rigidity of abdomen, which might indicate bowel perforation</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step17"><label>Document time of procedure and patients response</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step18"><label>Send patient to ward</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step19"><label>Monitor vital signs</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step20"><label>Provide calm environment and keep patient comfortable</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1></group></h:body></h:html>